    "These approaches rely on predefined rank schedules or heuristic-based adaptations, but they do not incorporate semantic feedback from the data and lack token-level guidance.",
    "Furthermore, these techniques do not explicitly address low-bit quantized training, limiting their compatibility with memoryconstrained hardware setups.",
    "Limitations of prior adaptive approaches.",
    "Despite their innovations, existing adaptive rank methods share several limitations: (1) they introduce substantial computational overhead due to expensive matrix decompositions and scoring steps; (2) they primarily focus on layer-level allocation without accounting for token-level importance, thereby missing opportunities to direct learning toward critical content; and (3) they are not designed with quantized environments in mind, making it challenging to integrate them with low-memory fine-tuning techniques such as QLoRA.",
    "These limitations highlight the need for approaches that are efficient, responsive to data-driven signals, and compatible with constrained hardware."
